The Wife actor Mondli Makhoba is preparing to launch his Bhut’Omdala Fedora Hats at the Mall of Africa’s Eyamilifestyle this week. The actor, who is also a motivational speaker and author, is fondly referred to by his character name Bhut’Omdala (older brother). On The Wife, he represents leadership, respect, and wisdom, the same vision he has for this brand. “This brand is set to enhance respect, leadership loyalty, family, love, and admiration through timeless and classy clothing,” he wrote. The Fedora hats are trimmed with eYami Fashion and Lifestyle unique prints. The collaboration has seen the two brands embracing values of culture and heritage.  For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.